# ─── Python cache artifacts ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Generated by Python, never commit these.
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.DS_Store
*.egg-info/

# ─── Labs / experimental run artifacts ───────────────────────────────────────
# Skill candidate runs, scratch outputs, temp files under labs/.
# These are local-only by design — do not commit.
labs/skills/*/candidate/
labs/skills/*/runs/
labs/skills/*/tmp/

# ─── Session transcripts backed up by precompact hook ────────────────────────
# The hook now writes to ~/.cache/episteme/backups/ instead of this repo,
# but keep this rule so any legacy backups/ directory stays untracked.
backups/

# ─── Per-project runtime surface/audit artifacts ─────────────────────────────
# Written by `episteme inject` and the reasoning_surface_guard hook.
# Local, regenerable, session-scoped — never commit.
.episteme/
.cognitive-os/

# ─── Local archive of superseded design rationale ────────────────────────────
# Files moved here are preserved for the operator's local reference but are
# intentionally not tracked in the repo (git history retains them at their
# pre-archive paths). See Event 54 in docs/PROGRESS.md for the move list.
/archive/

# ─── Personal episteme memory files ──────────────────────────────────────
# These ship with the repo as the author's real profiles (see core/memory/global/).
# Forks: edit them to make them your own, then run `episteme sync`.
#
# python_runtime_policy.md is gitignored because it contains machine-specific
# paths (Conda root) that differ per user. Run `episteme init` to generate it
# from examples/python_runtime_policy.example.md.
core/memory/global/python_runtime_policy.md

# ─── Machine-generated profile artifacts ─────────────────────────────────────
# Output of `episteme profile` and `episteme cognition` commands.
# Non-authoritative until compiled with --write. Local-only, don't commit.
core/memory/global/.generated/workstyle_profile.json
core/memory/global/.generated/workstyle_scores.json
core/memory/global/.generated/workstyle_explanations.md
core/memory/global/.generated/cognitive_profile.json
core/memory/global/.generated/cognitive_explanations.md
core/memory/global/.generated/personalization_blueprint.md

# ─── Evolution run files ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Output of `episteme evolve run`. Local-only episode records.
core/memory/evolution/episodes/*.json

# ─── Secrets and sensitive local artifacts ───────────────────────────────────
# Never commit credentials, tokens, local settings overrides, databases, or logs.
# These patterns cover common accidental-commit vectors.
.env
.env.*
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.pfx
*.crt
*.cer
*.der
secrets/
credentials/
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
*.db
*.log
*.tmp
*.bak
.cache/
.claude/settings.local.json
.codex/auth.json
.cursor/settings.local.json

# ─── Privatized strategic forward-vision docs (Event 65) ─────────────────────
# Moved to ~/episteme-private/docs/ per Path C step 1 (2026-04-27). Local
# symlinks at these paths point to the private staging dir for operator
# convenience; the public commit captures pure deletion. Re-publishing
# requires deleting the symlink and committing the file content from the
# private staging directory.
docs/DESIGN_V1_1_REASONING_ENGINE.md
docs/ROADMAP_POST_V1.md
docs/POST_SOAK_MIGRATION_PLAN.md
docs/POST_SOAK_TRIAGE.md

# ─── Privatized Tier 1 + Tier 2 docs (Event 66) ──────────────────────────────
# Operational/strategic docs moved to ~/episteme-private/docs/ per the broader
# Tier 1 (operational state) + Tier 2 (positioning narrative) classification.
# Same symlink pattern as Event 65. Tier 3 (DESIGN_V1_0, EVOLUTION_CONTRACT,
# ARCHITECTURE, LAYER_MODEL, SUBSTRATE_BRIDGE, MEMORY_CONTRACT) remains PUBLIC
# as the kernel's credibility surface — protected by AGPL-3.0.
docs/NEXT_STEPS.md
docs/PLAN.md
docs/PROGRESS.md
docs/DEFERRED_DISCOVERIES_TRIAGE.md
docs/DISCRIMINATOR_CALIBRATION.md
docs/PREPARED_PATCHES.md
docs/POSTURE.md
docs/NARRATIVE.md
docs/COGNITIVE_SYSTEM_PLAYBOOK.md
docs/DECISION_STORY.md
